@node Version 112
@section Version 1.1.2

@itemize
@item
Fix occasional errors like "The connected server(s) does not support
method @samp{$/lean/plainGoal}" by not wrapping invocations of
@code{lsp-protocol} macro into @code{eval-when-compile} but rather into
@code{eval-and-compile}.  Thus, the methods should now work, no matter
whether Lean4-Mode was loaded by interpreting @samp{.el} Elisp code or by
loading compiled @samp{.elc} or @samp{.eln} files.  (@uref{https://github.com/leanprover-community/lean4-mode/issues/54, Bug#54}, @uref{https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/channel/468104-Emacs/topic/lsp-mode.20errors.20due.20to.20list.20!.3D.20hash-table, Zulip discussion})
@end itemize

